Database Migration Process
Production Jira
 |
 |--- XML Backup (issues, users, config)
 |--- Jira Home Backup (attachments, avatars)
 |
 Pre Production Jira 
| 
|--- Empty PostgreSQL DB 
|--- Restore XML 
|--- Restore Attachments 
|--- Re Index

Step 1: Preparation
Validate Versions & Apps
On both Prod and Pre Prod:
•	Jira version → MUST match exactly
•	All Marketplace apps → Same versions
•	PostgreSQL version → Compatible

Steps 2: Need to Freez these activity in Production if they are impaction production
1>Disable Webhooks
•	Go to administrator ->System
•	Click webhooks
•	Click each webhooks and disable
2>Disabling script runner activities
•	Go to administrator –> Manage apps ->Script runner
•	Check and disable
o	Scheduled Jobs
o	Listeners
o	Custom REST endpoints
Note : Any jobs that’s create issues, sync data and calls external APIs
3>Disabling Jira Automation Rules
•	Go to administrator -> System -> Automation
•	Disable rules with
o	Incoming webhooks
o	Create issue
o	Sync external systems

4>Removing global permissions
•	Go to Administrator->System->Global permissions
•	Remove integration user/group from:
o	Create issues
o	Edit issues

Step 3: Production / Pre-production Backup
Full Jira XML Backup (MANDATORY)
Follow the same steps in production also in the pre-production
•	Login to Jira
•	Go to Administrator -> System ->System backup
•	Enter File name : prod_full_backup_2026_03_30
•	Give check mark on include attachments
•	Click backup
Backup location : <JIRA_HOME>/export/backups/
Note your taking backup for both prod and preprod

Stop jira service on before copying
$ stop-jira.sh

Even if attachments are included, Data Center requires manual copy.
•	<JIRA_HOME>/data/attachments
•	<JIRA_HOME>/data/avatars
•	<JIRA_HOME>/data/icons
•	<JIRA_HOME>/data/plugins
How to copy the above file into a backup folder
cp -R attachments/ 	<JIRA_HOME>/Export/backup/
cp -R avatars/     <JIRA_HOME>/Export/backup/
cp -R icons/       <JIRA_HOME>/Export/backup/
cp -R plugins/     <JIRA_HOME>/Export/backup/

Now start the Jira service after the copying is completed
$ start-jira.sh

Prepare Pre Production Database (PostgreSQL) Empty before restoring
•	Stop ALL Jira Pre Prod Nodes
•	Now login to PostgreSQL of Pre-Production
•	Login with super user
•	Now Run the JQL
-- Login as postgres user
psql -U postgres

DROP DATABASE jirapreprod;
CREATE DATABASE jirapreprod
  WITH OWNER=jirauser
  ENCODING='UTF8'
  LC_COLLATE='C'
  LC_CTYPE='C'
  TEMPLATE=template0;

Restoring Production XML Backup file in the pre-production

•	Now you need to start 1 jira node of pre-production.
•	If you have multiple nodes then let it be jira service is stopped for remaining nodes.
•	Now to start the 1 pre-production node
•	Open terminal and run the below command.
$ start-jira.sh
•	Now login to Jira from any browser
•	Go to Administrator->System->Restore system
•	Now select the path of production xml backfile
•	Choose outgoing email disable
•	Now click on restore

Restoring Jira Production Data
Now go to production Jira server node and open terminal and run the below command
rsync -avz \
/var/atlassian/application-data/jira/data/attachments \
jira@preprod-server:/var/atlassian/application-data/jira/data/

rsync -avz \
/var/atlassian/application-data/jira/data/avatars \
jira@preprod-server:/var/atlassian/application-data/jira/data/

rsync -avz \
/var/atlassian/application-data/jira/data/icons \
jira@preprod-server:/var/atlassian/application-data/jira/data/

rsync -avz \
/var/atlassian/application-data/jira/data/plugins \
jira@preprod-server:/var/atlassian/application-data/jira/data/


or

cp -R attachments/ <PREPROD_JIRA_HOME>/data/
cp -R avatars/     <PREPROD_JIRA_HOME>/data/
cp -R icons/       <PREPROD_JIRA_HOME>/data/
cp -R plugins/     <PREPROD_JIRA_HOME>/data/

Once the file is copied in the pre-production fix the permissions 
chown -R jira:jira /var/atlassian/application-data/jira
chmod -R 750 /var/atlassian/application-data/jira

Now start all the jira nodes
$ start-jira.sh

Full Re Index (REQUIRED) on pre-production
Administration → System → Indexing → Full Re index
Note : Restore will not complete without re indexing. 
Disable Email Notifications (IMPORTANT)
Always make sure the email notifications is disabled for pre-production
If not please follow the below steps
•	Log in to Jira Pre Production as System Admin 
•	Go to -> Administration → System 
•	Click Outgoing Mail 
•	You will see your SMTP server 
•	Click Disable 
•	Save

Now Update Environment Specific Settings
•	Go to Jira Administrator ->System->General setting
•	Click on edit setting
•	Title change it to : Jira Pre-Production
•	Base URL change it to : https://jira-preprod.company.com
•	Now go down and click on update

Check these below settings:
•	LDAP / SSO endpoints
•	Webhooks
•	CI/CD integrations
•	OAuth/API tokens

Final Validation Checklist 
Verify:
•	Projects list 
•	Issues & comments 
•	Attachments download 
•	Boards & dashboards 
•	User login 
•	Permissions 

Setting up announcement banner

Make sure before making pre-production refresh you need to update banner on both environments so user can be aware of this activity.

To set Follow the below steps
•	Login to Jira
•	Click on Jira Administrator -> System
•	Under user interface 
•	Click on announcement banner
•	Paste the below code
<div style="background-color:#fff3cd; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ffeeba;">
  <b style="color:#b30000;">
    ⚠️ PRE PRODUCTION REFRESH IN PROGRESS ⚠️
  </b>
  <br/><br/>
  This Jira <b>Pre Production</b> environment is undergoing a refresh.<br/>
  Data may change or be unavailable.
  <br/><br/>
  <b>⏰ Maintenance window:</b><br/>
  30 Mar 2026 | 18:00 – 22:00 IST
  <br/><br/>
  <b>Please do not use this environment during this period.</b>
</div>
•	Visibility set it as Public
•	Now click on set banner.
•	Once the above activity done make sure to remove this banner.


